                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./646:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-13T20:00:00-04:30"
                            >September 13, 1929—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 14—3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>148. You may desire to intimate informally to Pan American Airways that it might
                    be very helpful to them if Lindbergh could arrange to include Venezuela in his
                    next flight, as he was given great ovation last year. See Legation’s despatch
                    1473, February 3rd [<hi rend="italic">7th</hi>], 1928.<note n="39"
                        xml:id="d417fn39">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
